{"id":"exp-msgvault-20260314-183503-01","brief":"search-perf.md","hypothesis":"Bundle all per-Parse allocations into a single queryStore struct with embedded backing arrays for slice fields (TextTerms, FromAddrs, etc.) and inline storage for dates/sizes. This converts 12 separate heap allocations (Query + 6 slice growths + 2 date pointers + 2 size pointers + token slice) into 2 allocations (queryStore + token slice), reducing GC pressure and malloc overhead.","files_changed":["internal/search/parser.go"],"metric_before":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":1105,"bench_parse_bare_ns":106.3,"bench_parse_operators_ns":550.1,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"metric_after":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":592.4,"bench_parse_bare_ns":77.93,"bench_parse_operators_ns":309.5,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"kept":false,"status":"success","duration_s":684,"token_cost_usd":1.7551235000000003,"timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:46:28Z","model":"opus","input_tokens":21,"output_tokens":33366,"wave_id":null}
{"id":"exp-msgvault-20260314-183503-02","brief":"search-perf.md","hypothesis":"Replace strings.Builder-based tokenizer with index-tracking that returns zero-copy substrings of the original query string, eliminating ~32 allocations from Builder.String() calls and buffer growth. For most tokens (non-quoted words, operator:value, double-quoted phrases), the token is an exact substring of the input, so a slice reference avoids allocation entirely. Only single-quoted standalone phrases (rare) require a new string.","files_changed":["internal/search/parser.go"],"metric_before":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":1105,"bench_parse_bare_ns":106.3,"bench_parse_operators_ns":550.1,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"metric_after":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":724.3,"bench_parse_bare_ns":116.8,"bench_parse_operators_ns":375.9,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"kept":false,"status":"success","duration_s":684,"token_cost_usd":0.8604762499999998,"timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:46:28Z","model":"opus","input_tokens":13,"output_tokens":15225,"wave_id":null}
{"id":"exp-msgvault-20260314-184628-03","brief":"search-perf.md","hypothesis":"Replace time.Parse with manual digit extraction + time.Date() for date parsing, and replace strconv.ParseFloat with manual integer parsing for size values. time.Parse is ~250ns per call due to format scanning and timezone logic; manual digit extraction + time.Date() is ~20ns. For 2 dates + 2 sizes in the complex benchmark, this eliminates ~400ns of stdlib overhead.","files_changed":["internal/search/parser.go"],"metric_before":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":1105,"bench_parse_bare_ns":106.3,"bench_parse_operators_ns":550.1,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"metric_after":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":523.4,"bench_parse_bare_ns":76.45,"bench_parse_operators_ns":283.0,"coverage":98.8,"test_count":99},"kept":false,"status":"success","duration_s":548,"token_cost_usd":0.634885,"timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:55:36Z","model":"opus","input_tokens":13,"output_tokens":10367,"wave_id":null}
{"id":"exp-msgvault-20260314-184628-04","brief":"search-perf.md","hypothesis":"Eliminate the tokens []string slice allocation by inlining tokenization directly into Parse(). Instead of calling tokenize() to build a slice then iterating over it, process each token inline via a closure as it is discovered during the character scan. This removes 1 of 2 remaining heap allocations (the make([]string, 0, cap) call) and avoids the double-pass overhead of first building then iterating the token list.","files_changed":["internal/search/parser.go"],"metric_before":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":1105,"bench_parse_bare_ns":106.3,"bench_parse_operators_ns":550.1,"coverage":100.0,"test_count":99},"metric_after":{"pass_rate":1,"bench_parse_complex_ns":375.7,"bench_parse_bare_ns":58.79,"bench_parse_operators_ns":204.8,"coverage":98.7,"test_count":99},"kept":false,"status":"success","duration_s":548,"token_cost_usd":1.3590722499999999,"timestamp":"2026-03-14T18:55:36Z","model":"opus","input_tokens":18,"output_tokens":23615,"wave_id":null}
